{"id": "EUVD-2022-54617", "enisaUuid": "91c23d28-593d-302c-aa06-8e9ee42b2353", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: rt711-sdca: fix kernel NULL pointer dereference when IO error\n\nThe initial settings will be written before the codec probe function.\nBut, the rt711->component doesn't be assigned yet.\nIf IO error happened during initial settings operations, it will cause the kernel panic.\nThis patch changed component->dev to slave->dev to fix this issue.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:23:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:36:51", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/269be8b2907378adf72d7347cfa43ef230351a06", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7bb71133cae88d3003a3490b97864af76533072b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1df793d479bef546569fc2e409ff8bb3f0fb8e99"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49615"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "294695f7-435f-3737-90de-a2b623068c9f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.13"}, {"id": "6549d7f0-a60a-32ae-9c35-aaf9cf0a0ba4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7ad4d237e7c4a5dcc71cf438f646744b4484f1da <1df793d479bef546569fc2e409ff8bb3f0fb8e99"}, {"id": "6803cf04-e979-3231-8503-c37664f5abcc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7ad4d237e7c4a5dcc71cf438f646744b4484f1da <7bb71133cae88d3003a3490b97864af76533072b"}, {"id": "92b36223-b8ce-3b9c-9e28-8a1809595c05", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <269be8b2907378adf72d7347cfa43ef230351a06"}, {"id": "9c8e0c57-82e2-3a95-a68b-66ffab55d18c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "9eb18ef2-5a57-3861-8754-f450c7299053", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <1df793d479bef546569fc2e409ff8bb3f0fb8e99"}, {"i